Overview
========

edgar is a small LISP Interpreter written in C.

Build Dependencies (i.e. dependencies needed to compile)
========================================================

 - libgmp - GNU MP http://gmplib.org/
 - C toolchain: C compiler, linker, assembler, libc, etc.

Check Dependencies (i.e. dependencies for running the test suite)
=================================================================

 - libgmp - GNU MP http://gmplib.org/
- diff
- valgrind (optional) - http://valgrind.org/

Runtime Dependencies (i.e. dependencies needed once installed)
==============================================================

 - libgmp - GNU MP http://gmplib.org/

Building
========

Standard autotools build (`make check` runs the test suite):

	$ autoreconf -i
 	$ ./configure --prefix=/usr
	$ make
	$ make check
	# make install

Note: `autoreconf -i` is only needed if there is no configure script.
